    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@cburgdorf I think atomic batch has to be implemented on the client side of the two processes, wrapping the proxy DB such that it knows how to do the atomic batching locally.\r\n\r\ncc @carver as I think we figured out that due to the concurrency/async nature of the code that we can't reasonably do batching from the perspective of the database process because we can't constrain which *things* are part of the batch and which aren't (i.e. two different processes writing, one starts a batch, from the db perspective it can't differentiate which writes should be part of the batch and which shouldn't).",
